On the contrary to our hypothesis, ErMF showed higher affinity to spruce roots decomposing in bare soil and CWD microhabitats. Ericoid mycorrhizal fungi possess the ability to form endophytic association with non-ericoid mycorrhizal plants (
 Chambers et al., 2008; 
 Kohout et al., 2013). Therefore, the ericoid plant shrubs do not represent the only suitable habitat for ErMF. Why some ErMF preferentially colonize decomposing spruce roots remains an open question.
